<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 1
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1>Detailed Change Log</h1>

<div class="change-block purple">
  <div class="change-number">Change 01 · 02 April 2026 · New Feature</div>
  <div class="change-title">Staff Strength Register — New Module</div>
  <p>A new Staff Strength Register module was built from scratch. Each institution is required to submit an annual staff headcount report detailing sanctioned vs filled posts across all teaching and program categories. HOI fills and submits; FDE Cell reviews, edits, and locks the record.</p>
</div>

<h3>Database Migrations Created</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Migration File</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">2026_04_02_..._create_staff_post_types_table.php</span></td><td>Stores all post types: Principal, VP, SST, SET, EST, ECE, TFP, DIL, Coding Fellow, etc.</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">2026_04_02_..._create_staff_strength_registers_table.php</span></td><td>Main register per institution per academic year. Tracks status: draft / submitted / locked</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">2026_04_02_..._create_staff_strength_entries_table.php</span></td><td>Per-row entries: sanctioned_posts, filled_posts, sacked, deputationist in/out, temporary in/out, daily_wagers</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Models Created</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Model</th><th>Location</th><th>Key Features</th></tr>
  <tr><td>StaffPostType</td><td><span class="code-inline">app/Models/StaffPostType.php</span></td><td>forLevel() scope — filters post types by school type (I-V, I-VIII, VI-X etc.)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>StaffStrengthRegister</td><td><span class="code-inline">app/Models/StaffStrengthRegister.php</span></td><td>isDraft(), isSubmitted(), isLocked() helpers. totalPresentOnDuty() calculation</td></tr>
  <tr><td>StaffStrengthEntry</td><td><span class="code-inline">app/Models/StaffStrengthEntry.php</span></td><td>Computed accessor: vacant_posts = max(0, sanctioned_posts − filled_posts)</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Seeder Created</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>File</th><th>Content</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">database/seeders/StaffPostTypeSeeder.php</span></td><td>Seeds 18 post types (10 teaching + 8 program). Each post type maps to applicable school levels using JSON array. Run once: <span class="code-inline">php artisan db:seed --class=StaffPostTypeSeeder</span></td></tr>
</table>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 2
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 02 · 05 April 2026 · New Feature</div>
  <div class="change-title">Merit List Feature — Full Build (Model, Controllers, Views, Routes)</div>
  <p>The Merit List module was built end-to-end. HOI users can upload merit list files (PDF, Excel, CSV) for their school. The public portal displays all uploaded merit lists with download links. FDE Cell has an admin view to manage lists across all schools.</p>
</div>

