<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 4
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block red" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 04 · 10 April 2026 · Bug Fix</div>
  <div class="change-title">Merit List Public Portal — 500 Server Error</div>
</div>

<div class="label-box">Problem</div>
<p>The public portal merit lists page at <span class="code-inline">/portal/merit-lists</span> was throwing a 500 Internal Server Error immediately on load. The error log showed: <em>"Call to undefined method App\Models\InstitutionMeritList::fileIcon()"</em></p>

<div class="label-box note">Root Cause</div>
<p>The Blade view called three methods on the model that were referenced in the view but never defined in the model class: <span class="code-inline">fileIcon()</span>, <span class="code-inline">fileType()</span>, and <span class="code-inline">isNew()</span>.</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Fix Applied</div>
<p>Added all three missing methods to <span class="code-inline">app/Models/InstitutionMeritList.php</span>:</p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Returns</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">fileIcon()</span></td><td>Emoji icon: 📄 for PDF, 📊 for Excel, 📋 for CSV, 📁 default</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">fileType()</span></td><td>Human label: "PDF Document", "Excel Spreadsheet", "CSV File"</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">isNew()</span></td><td>Returns true if file was uploaded within the last 7 days (shows "New" badge)</td></tr>
</table>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 5
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block red" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 05 · 12 April 2026 · Bug Fix</div>
  <div class="change-title">Hostinger Live Server — Merit List Download 404 Error</div>
</div>

<div class="label-box">Problem</div>
<p>After the 500 error was fixed, clicking the Download button on any merit list file returned a 404 Not Found error on the live Hostinger server. Files were being uploaded successfully but could not be retrieved.</p>

<div class="label-box note">Root Cause</div>
<p>Hostinger's LiteSpeed web server does not serve files from the <span class="code-inline">public/storage/</span> directory as static files when it is a real folder (not a symlink). The <span class="code-inline">php artisan storage:link</span> command creates a symlink, but Hostinger does not honour symlinks in shared hosting.</p>
<p>Additionally, the filesystem disk root was pointing to <span class="code-inline">storage/app/public</span> (the default Laravel path) rather than <span class="code-inline">public/storage</span> (where Hostinger's web root expects files).</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Fix Applied — 4 Files Changed</div>

<h3>1. config/filesystems.php</h3>
<p>Changed the <span class="code-inline">public</span> disk root so files write directly to the web-accessible path:</p>
<span class="code">// BEFORE
'root' => storage_path('app/public'),

// AFTER
'root' => public_path('storage'),</span>

<h3>2. routes/web.php — Added PHP-Served Download Route</h3>
<p>Added a route that serves files through PHP, bypassing the web server's static file restrictions entirely:</p>
<span class="code">Route::get('/merit-file/{meritList}', function (InstitutionMeritList $meritList) {
    $disk = Storage::disk('public');
    if (! $disk->exists($meritList->file_path)) {
        abort(404, 'File not found.');
    }
    return $disk->response($meritList->file_path, $meritList->original_name);
})->name('merit.file');</span>

<h3>3 &amp; 4. portal/show.blade.php and portal/merit_lists.blade.php</h3>
<p>Updated all download links from <span class="code-inline">asset('storage/' . $ml->file_path)</span> to <span class="code-inline">$ml->downloadUrl()</span> which now resolves to the new named route.</p>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 6
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block red" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 06 · 14 April 2026 · Bug Fix</div>
  <div class="change-title">Baseline Enrollment — "Failed" Count Not Saving or Displaying</div>
</div>

<div class="label-box">Problem</div>
<p>On the Baseline Enrollment page, HOI users enter two values per class: <strong>Promoted</strong> (students passed from previous class) and <strong>Failed</strong> (students repeating the same class). Entering a value in the Failed field had absolutely no effect — it was not saved to the database and always displayed as 0.</p>

<div class="label-box note">Root Cause</div>
<p>Three separate points in the data flow were broken simultaneously:</p>
<ol>
  <li>The controller <strong>save()</strong> method only saved <span class="code-inline">existing_enrollment</span> (promoted + failed total) and never saved <span class="code-inline">promoted_count</span> or <span class="code-inline">failed_count</span> individually</li>
  <li>The Alpine.js component initialized both fields from <span class="code-inline">existing_enrollment</span> and a hardcoded <span class="code-inline">0</span>, not from the actual DB columns</li>
  <li>The locked (read-only) view displayed <span class="code-inline">{{ number_format($ic->failed_count) }}</span> but the column was always 0 because it was never written</li>
</ol>

<div class="label-box fix">Fix Applied — 2 Files Changed</div>

<h3>app/Http/Controllers/Hoi/EnrollmentController.php</h3>
<span class="code">// BEFORE — only saved total
$ic->update([
    'existing_enrollment' => $promoted + $failed,
    'enrollment_status'   => $action === 'submit' ? 'verified' : 'draft',
]);

// AFTER — saves all three columns
$ic->update([
    'existing_enrollment' => $promoted + $failed,
    'promoted_count'      => $promoted,
    'failed_count'        => $failed,
    'enrollment_status'   => $action === 'submit' ? 'verified' : 'draft',
]);</span>

<h3>resources/views/hoi/enrollment/index.blade.php</h3>
<p>Three fixes in this view file:</p>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Alpine.js <span class="code-inline">rows</span> now initializes from <span class="code-inline">promoted_count</span> and <span class="code-inline">failed_count</span> DB columns</li>
  <li>Form inputs now have correct name attributes: <span class="code-inline">enrollment[N][promoted]</span> and <span class="code-inline">enrollment[N][failed]</span></li>
  <li>Locked (submitted) view now reads <span class="code-inline">$ic->promoted_count</span> and <span class="code-inline">$ic->failed_count</span> instead of showing 0</li>
</ul>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 7
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block green" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 07 · 15 April 2026 · Enhancement</div>
  <div class="change-title">FDE Merit Lists — Live Search Filter + EMIS Code in Dropdown</div>
</div>

<p><strong>File Modified:</strong> <span class="code-inline">resources/views/fde/merit_lists/index.blade.php</span></p>

<div class="label-box note">Problem</div>
<p>The FDE Merit List management page had no search functionality. With hundreds of institutions, finding a specific school required scrolling through the entire page. Also, the institution dropdown in the upload form showed only the school name with no EMIS code, making it difficult to identify the correct school when multiple schools have similar names.</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Changes Made</div>
<ul class="checklist">
  <li>Added an Alpine.js live search bar — filters institution cards in real-time as the user types a school name or EMIS number</li>
  <li>Added a "No results" message when the search finds no matching schools</li>
  <li>Updated the upload form's institution dropdown to show: <span class="code-inline">[EMIS: 1234] School Name</span></li>
  <li>Search works on both the school name and the EMIS code simultaneously</li>
</ul>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 8
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 08 · 16 April 2026 · Enhancement</div>
  <div class="change-title">Daily Admissions — Unified Table with Morning/Evening Shift Toggle</div>
</div>

<p><strong>File Modified:</strong> <span class="code-inline">resources/views/hoi/admissions/daily.blade.php</span></p>

<div class="label-box note">Problem</div>
<p>The Daily Admissions page displayed two completely separate full-width tables — one for Morning Shift and one for Evening Shift — stacked vertically. HOI users had to scroll far down to reach the Evening Shift table. For morning-only schools, the Evening table was still rendered but was empty and unused.</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Changes Made</div>
<p>The two separate tables were merged into a single unified table. A pill-style toggle button appears above the table for schools with an evening shift:</p>

<table>
  <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Toggle button</td><td>🌅 Morning Shift (blue) | 🌆 Evening Shift (indigo) — only shown if school has evening shift</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Reactive columns</td><td>Regular Boys/Girls, OOSC Boys/Girls, P2G Boys/Girls, Today's Total — all switch based on active tab</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Morning-only schools</td><td>No toggle shown at all — clean single-table view</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Data integrity</td><td>All 12 shift fields still submitted to the server — no data lost when switching tabs</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Old table</td><td>Hidden with @if(false) — not deleted, preserved for reference</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Alpine.js Additions</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Variable / Function</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">activeShift: 'morning'</span></td><td>Tracks which shift tab is currently active</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">shiftRowTotal(cls)</span></td><td>Sums the 6 input fields for the currently active shift only (used in Today's Total column)</td></tr>
  <tr><td><span class="code-inline">rowTotal(cls)</span></td><td>Retained — sums all 12 fields across both shifts (used for capacity checks)</td></tr>
</table>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 9
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block red" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 09 · 19 April 2026 · Bug Fix</div>
  <div class="change-title">Daily Admissions — All Classes Showing "Full" / Available = 0</div>
</div>

<p><strong>File Modified:</strong> <span class="code-inline">app/Http/Controllers/Hoi/DailyAdmissionController.php</span></p>

<div class="label-box">Problem</div>
<p>Every class on the Daily Admissions page was showing <strong>Available = 0</strong> and the red "🚫 Full" badge, even for classes where Total Seats = 40 and Existing Students = 14 (Available should be 26). The entire admissions table was disabled and HOI users could not enter any data.</p>

<div class="label-box note">Root Cause</div>
<p>The available seats formula subtracted cumulative admissions from all prior days (<span class="code-inline">$cumRegular</span>) from the available count:</p>
<span class="code">// WRONG formula
$available = max(0, $ic->total_seats - $ic->existing_enrollment - $cumRegular);</span>
<p>Schools that had any historical test/draft admission records had a large <span class="code-inline">$cumRegular</span> value, making <span class="code-inline">available = 0</span>. The formula counted ALL prior day records regardless of their status (draft, submitted, verified).</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Fix Applied</div>
<p>Simplified the formula to match the user-defined business logic: Available = Total Seats − Existing Enrollment (static capacity, does not decrease with daily admissions):</p>
<span class="code">// CORRECT formula
$available = max(0, $ic->total_seats - $ic->existing_enrollment);</span>

<table>
  <tr><th>Example</th><th>Before Fix</th><th>After Fix</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Total=40, Existing=14, Prior Admissions=26</td><td>Available = 0 (🚫 Full)</td><td>Available = 26 ✅</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Total=50, Existing=20, Prior Admissions=0</td><td>Available = 30 ✅</td><td>Available = 30 ✅</td></tr>
</table>


<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
     CHANGE 10
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="change-block orange" style="margin-top:18pt;">
  <div class="change-number">Change 10 · 19 April 2026 · Enhancement</div>
  <div class="change-title">Daily Admissions — "⚙️ Not Set" Badge for Unconfigured Classes</div>
</div>

<p><strong>File Modified:</strong> <span class="code-inline">resources/views/hoi/admissions/daily.blade.php</span></p>

<div class="label-box note">Problem</div>
<p>When a class had <span class="code-inline">total_seats = 0</span> in the database (because the HOI never entered a value in Class Setup, or the field defaulted to 0), the class appeared with the "🚫 Full" badge — the same badge used for genuinely full classes. This was confusing and misleading because the class was not full, it had simply never been configured.</p>

<div class="label-box fix">Changes Made</div>

<table>
  <tr><th>State</th><th>Old Behaviour</th><th>New Behaviour</th></tr>
  <tr><td>total_seats = 0 (not configured)</td><td>🚫 Full (red) — row greyed out and disabled</td><td>⚙️ Not Set (amber) — row visible, yellow background</td></tr>
  <tr><td>total_seats &gt; 0, available = 0 (genuinely full)</td><td>🚫 Full (red) — correct</td><td>🚫 Full (red) — unchanged ✅</td></tr>
  <tr><td>total_seats &gt; 0, available &gt; 0 (open)</td><td>No badge — correct</td><td>No badge — unchanged ✅</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Alpine.js Changes</h3>
<span class="code">// NEW function
isNotConfigured(cls) {
    return cls.total_seats === 0;
},

// UPDATED function — now only fires for genuinely full classes
isFull(cls) {
    return cls.total_seats > 0 && cls.available <= 0;
},</span>


